    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-11-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-11-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="661"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d661">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861b.6363/86</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Sinclair Exploration Company</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-11-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 1, 1923</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Gentlemen</hi>: The Department is in receipt of your letter
                    of October 24, 1923, stating that your company has recently despatched a party
                    to the Far East with instructions to proceed to the “Russian half of the Island
                    of Sakhalin, and there commence exploratory work for oil.” You add that “this
                    work is undertaken in fulfillment of the concessional contract, for the
                    exploration and development of the oil resources of Sakhalin, originally entered
                    into between the <pb facs="0936" n="812" xml:id="pg_812"/> Sinclair Exploration
                    Company and the Far Eastern Republic, and since ratified in August of this year
                    by the Moscow Government.”</p>
                <p>In acknowledging the receipt of your letter this Department refers you to its
                    letter of March 17, 1923.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>For the Secretary of State:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">William Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                    <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Under Secretary</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
